        <h1>Article 31B: Validation of certain Acts and Regulations</h1>
        <p>
          * Article 31B of the Indian Constitution provides protection to
          certain laws and regulations from being challenged in court,
          specifically those listed in the Ninth Schedule.
        </p>
        <p>
          * Article 31B shields laws included in the Ninth Schedule of the
          Constitution from legal challenges. This means that these laws cannot
          be contested in court on the grounds that they violate fundamental
          rights.
        </p>
        <p>
          * The Ninth Schedule is a list that includes laws related to land
          reforms, property rights, and other social and economic measures
          deemed important by the government. These laws are protected under
          Article 31B to ensure they can be implemented without being struck
          down by courts.
        </p>
        <p>
          * In summary, Article 31B ensures that laws listed in the Ninth
          Schedule are protected from legal challenges, helping to stabilize
          important reforms and policies.
        </p>
      </div>
