          * Article 31C of the Indian Constitution provides special protection
          to laws aimed at implementing the Directive Principles of State
          Policy, particularly those related to social and economic justice.
        </p>
        <p>
          * Article 31C ensures that laws made to promote the Directive
          Principles of State Policy, especially those related to social and
          economic justice, cannot be challenged in court for violating
          fundamental rights
        </p>
        <p>
          * These principles are guidelines for the government to promote
          welfare and justice in society, such as ensuring equitable
          distribution of resources and improving living conditions.
        </p>
        <p>
          * In simple terms, Article 31C protects laws that are made to achieve
          social and economic goals from being challenged in court, even if they
          impact fundamental rights
        </p>
